{
  "stem": "1733.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So there was, between the roof of the shed and the cellar-- which was made out of dirt-- was room, and my grandmother was hiding some shoe leather over there.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And one shabbos afternoon, the gendarme, the Hungarian police, came over.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Three of them came over.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they were on a friendly basis, and they said that they found-- somebody reported us, that we were hiding some merchandise.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it's against the law to hold that, and so forth and so on, that we were black marketing it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they were looking all over-- they couldn't find it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Finally, they went up to the shed, and they were looking all over.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I was standing on the outside, and my mother was standing next to me, looking up at the police looking for that stuff, for the contraband stuff.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he picked up a board in the shed, and he saw it-- he saw the leather there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He took a look at my mother, and my mother went like that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He covered it up and he walked out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He did not do nothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was one of the local police that we knew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- who turned us in?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We didn't feel the effects of the Germans, but there were-- there were Hungarian laws they were following pretty closely, that the Jews had to be identified with yellow stars, and we had to wear them at all times.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if you didn't wear the stars, you were punished.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So these things were going on, and as the time was going on, it was getting worse and worse.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
